               <scopecontent id="aspace_2b7f604af89428c34b1e348315876449">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The formal invitation came from the President and Fellows of Yale University but responses were to be sent to the Dean of the School of Medicine. Speakers included Wilmarth S. Lewis, representing the Yale Corporation; Starling W. Childs representing Harvey Cushing's Yale Class of 1891; Charles Seymour, President of Yale University; Francis G. Blake, Dean of the School of Medicine; John Homans, a Harvard surgeon who had recently spent a year at Yale; and the Rev. George Stewart, Minister of the First Presbyterian Church, Stamford, and son-in-law of Arnold C. Klebs.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
